-- Argentina's Amado Boudou May Run For Mayor of Buenos Aires, Infobae Says
-- B y   E l i a n a   R a s z e w s k i
-- 2010-12-15T16:24:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/argentina-s-boudou-to-run-for-buenos-aires-mayor-infobae-says.html
Argentina’s Economy Minister  Amado Boudou  will run for mayor of the city of Buenos Aires next year,
newspaper Infobae reported.  Boudou’s candidacy will be announced on Dec. 21, the Buenos
Aires-based newspaper said, citing Omar Viviani, head of the
taxi drivers union, who met with Boudou last night.  An official at the Economy Ministry, who asked not to be
identified due to internal policies, told Bloomberg News that 
some political and labor leaders want Boudou to run.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eliana Raszewski in Buenos Aires at 
 eraszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  